{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1738', 'title': u'Embassy Suites by Hilton Chicago Downtown Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'600 North State Street, Chicago, IL 60654', 'review_list': [u'Friendly staff, free hot breakfast, free happy two hours! Indoor pool was well maintained and adequate workout facilities. Very comfortable rooms .we had a king bed suite with a frig and microwave.The room was very clean also.', u'Wonderful hotel! Excellent service,food,etc..... We were in this hotel 4 nights and everything was great! We loved the room in general, very clean, big & very comfortable. Front desk guys are very nice and helpful, we arrived very early, then we asked if they can keep our suit cases till check in time, but they said that our room was...\n\n\nMore', u"This is the nicest Embassy Suites in which I've ever stayed. It's open, airy and very clean. The room was standard but comfortable. No view, as we were in the back of the hotel, but it was quiet. (Some reviewers have mentioned street noise and I thought it very creative that bedside earplugs were provided, along with an explanation of...\n\n\nMore", u'One of the nicest hotels in downtown Chicago. Lobby and dining areas are large, airy and well appointed. My room was fantastic - very large, clean, modern and had great city views. Elevators were extremely fast which is always a plus. Cook to order breakfast can be a little slow, but the quality of the food was excellent.', u"We've stayed at the Embassy Suites Downtown on a number of occasions and keep returning. It's an excellent location, they offer great packages that include parking, and the suites are very comfortable. A wonderful breakfast buffet and evening cocktail hour are included with your stay, and all of that makes it a hard deal to beat! The only slightly negative...\n\n\nMore", u'Do not believe whatever the customer service line says parking is not free\nBut once you do get to the hotel great customer service all the time available for you nice clean rooms and bathrooms we requested for a king-size nonsuite but we got upgraded to king-size suite for free it was just a great experience this is the only...\n\n\nMore', u"I'm in Chicago 4-6 times a year. I usually stay at the Embassy on North Colombus but they were booked. It is in better condition then the No. Columbus location however the noise from the pool was a drab and went well into the night as it is located in the center of the hotel. There were so many children...\n\n\nMore", u"Each January I have a corporate event at a different hotel, but I choose to stay here for several great reasons: 1) cheaper than where my colleagues stay 2) larger room than where my colleagues stay 3) separate living room for comfort 4) free breakfast 5) free social hour. I haven't gone wrong yet. The only reason it wasn't 5...\n\n\nMore", u"Well, this trip has been interesting...usually we stay at the embassy .4 miles away (we didn't know this one existed) however, we soon found out this was the one we booked. This hotel is updated, clean, and staff are friendly. The prices a night, are very affordable...however the valet is highway robbery! Love the complimentary services here! We went for...\n\n\nMore", u"Within walking distance to miracle mile.Staff helpful and professional service. Ten dollar cab ride from train station. You can chose to walk' Would not suggest walking in sub zero temps. My visit was in January."], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/08/f3/83/21/nighttime-exterior.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1390', 'title': u'The Langham, Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'5.0', 'address': u'330 North Wabash Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'Stayed at the Langham the weekend of Jan 30th for two nights. It was definitely worth the price!! Luxury all the way! From the staff to the room itself, it was all very welcoming and spectacular. Will definitely be going back! Thank you James for the anniversary gift that was sent to our room. They definitely pay attention to detail...\n\n\nMore', u'From the moment you step into the lobby of the new Langham hotel in Chicago you cannot help but be impressed. The staff are super friendly and efficient and the lobby is chic, while maintaining the elegance you have come to expect from the Langham hotels.\nThe rooms are beautiful and comfortable, with intuitive design and a warm and inviting...\n\n\nMore', u'This hotel has ruined me. I measure all my hotel stays to this one. I have stayed at the W, the Omni, Four seasons, Ritz...they are all now "just ok" to me. Simplistically beautiful rooms. Amazing sheets. Great hospitality from the concierge to bartenders to room service staff. One of my favorite hotel gyms. There is absolutely nothing I don\'t...\n\n\nMore', u'I cannot say enough wonderful things about The Langham. The service from everyone is top notch, and the rooms are spectacular. They have every amenity you could possibly reach for. The bed is luxurious and the bathroom and tub are so lovely and inviting. I love the rain showerhead in the shower and all the bathroom amenities are so wonderful....\n\n\nMore', u'This is an upscale hotel that offers a great view of the Chicago river and even Lake Michigan. The staff and service is great. From the time when you first walk in the front entrance, the staff is more than helpful to guide you and to get you where you need to be.', u"My husband and I stayed here for a couple of nights in December. The hotel is beyond luxurious. Everyone, from the doorman to the waiters were professional and friendly. We also enjoyed the Langham Club amenities, which included an endless amount of snacks, hors d' oeuvres and a plethora of waters, sodas and juices. It also included a breakfast Buffett....\n\n\nMore", u"There really isn't much to say about this hotel that hasn't already been said. The Langham is in a class of its own. The staff at the hotel is wonderful. They are professional without being stuffy. I felt extremely welcomed by everyone I interacted with at the hotel. I also really appreciated the large and well designed bathroom. Having a...\n\n\nMore", u'The Langham, Chicago really is a beautiful, luxurious hotel. Exceptionally clean, beautifully designed, smells delicious and centrally located. Of course it is on the pricey side but you are paying for luxury and it does make you feel like a million bucks. If you can afford it, I highly recommend The Langham.', u'Superb hotel but the staff made it all the better if that were possible. Great artwork is wonderful, but the people that work here make it what it is. Hope to be back later in the year. Stayed at the Peninsula many times before which is lovely, but for me, the staff here went that extra mile. Timothy in the...\n\n\nMore', u'We travel to Chicago every November for a professional convention. We have tried many other hotels in the area. This hotel is magnificent. The decor is simply beautiful. The staff extremely friendly and the room delightful. I would not stay anywhere else even though the convention is at another hotel whether nearby (walking distance) or a cab ride away. I...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-p/09/4d/cb/dd/the-langham-chicago-exterior.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'3233', 'title': u'Sofitel Chicago Water Tower Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'20 East Chestnut St - Downtown, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u"One of my favorites. Great views from floor to ceiling windows (not sure if all rooms have this but try to get if you can). Beds are amazingly comfortable. Room service quick and efficient - great food! Bathrooms have cozy robes, hairdryers and some really good products. counter space could be larger - why don't hotels realize that women travel...\n\n\nMore", u"Location is convenient and not as touristic as other hotels. Concierge and Front Desk did a great job to help us getting around in the city. Room service is very nice and punctual. Rooms are spacious and have fantastic views of the city. We didn't tried the breakfast but you can get a coffee to go on the way out...\n\n\nMore", u"I stayed in this hotel for 5 days during my first visit to Chicago. I have to say for this price, this is the best hotel ever. You cannot ask for anything else. The location is great, it's couple of blocks away from the best shopping street in the world. Everything is spot on. It's next to YSL and just...\n\n\nMore", u'I had a lovely one night stay here. The room was a good size and the bed was very comfortable. The hotel is a short walk to the Water Tower shopping mall and there are eating options nearby. The hotel staff were all very kind and friendly.', u"We stay here once a year at least when we visit Chicago for the boat show. It's always a wonderful experience. The staff are among the best I've ever encountered--respectful, friendly and helpful. The rooms are beautiful and the views even on the lower floors are spectacular. You are right downtown and the energy and dynamic of that infuses the...\n\n\nMore", u'Cleanliness, location quality of food all excellent. Nothing too much for the staff. The exquisite smell when you walk in is intoxicating. Would definitely recommend. The attention to those finishing touches in the room is excellent', u"My 4-day stay at the Sofitel was lovely. The room was clean and quiet..so what more could you ask for! The staff was friendly and helpful. I don't understand complaints I've read about the workout room. It was fine- I expected it to be smaller based on some of the comments I've read.\nI thought it was a bargain for...\n\n\nMore", u'Thank you to the Sofitel for creating a wonderful birthday experience. My husband took me here on my 30th birthday and surprised me with a stay for my 40th. All the staff members we encountered - from the front desk to the valet - were friendly and helpful. My husband requested a room with a view and we ended up...\n\n\nMore', u"The weekend was built around a two night stay at the Sofitel. This was a celebration for a family member 'besting a serious medical issue'. The husband/wife that stayed at the Hotel was able to use all of the facilities offered to them from the Hotel to bring together the extended family for the two days of dinners, musicals and...\n\n\nMore", u'Well appointed hotel with gracious reception. Rooms are very comfortable conducive to work as well as rest. Perfectly located for business as well as shopping on mag mile. Amenities easy to use with great staff. Definitely home away from home.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-p/01/59/51/74/sofitel-chicago-water.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2016', 'title': u'The Talbott Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'5.0', 'address': u'20 East Delaware Place, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'A very nice boutique hotel but I would not rate as high as Tripadvisor has it. The room is adequate. A little small for me. The decor was traditional, the room was clean, the bath was small but adequate. It had all the electronic amenities which did not cost extra. Unfortunately, my window looked out against the building next to...\n\n\nMore', u'The Talbott hotel provided a therapeutic night out. Why pay a weekly session for couples therapy when you can take your loved one to this beatiful cosy hotel? ! They even upgraded us to a suite with a living room and kitchen. Great service, extremely comfortable beds, easy parking across the street, and spaciuos quarters.', u"My stay was fantastic. The hotel was walking distance to everything and the staff was outstanding. Got a great deal on the rooms. Would highly recommend.\nFirst time visiting Chicago and I'm glad I saw this deal on trip advisor.", u'Dwayne is the best doorman i have ever met. The hotel is charming in every detail and every staff member caters to your needs. The service is impeccable with smiles and kindness a continuous process. Thank you all at the talbott especially dwayne\nVegas showgirls\U0001f604', u'This hotel is an excellent location.\nThey staff is all happy and have the best service.\nThe room has more amenities that others, example, all the extra items in the bathroom, complimentary robe to use, two separate vanities in our 1 bedroom suite, great beds, Do not disturb light instead of card, (kind of cool), doorbell, free wifi and computer...\n\n\nMore', u'In the heart of Chicago, just off Michigan avenue. The Talbot hardens back to the grand old hotel tradition - personal service, the feeling of being at home and cared for. The staff is friendly, incredibly helpful, and seem to know what you need before you know it yourself. If you want to feel at home in the big city,...\n\n\nMore', u'We are currently staying here based on trip advisor reviews..\nWonderful location... Outstanding staff everybody is friendly, makes eye contact and says hello... The building itself is a classic, beautiful wood, fireplaces and decor....\nOur room is very comfortable, the bed, the furniture, even the towels and the soaps are all first class.\nThese are all good reasons why it...\n\n\nMore', u'A quick birthday getaway became a luxurious celebration thanks to the wonderful Talbott team. The charming and efficient check-in staff upgraded us to to a marvelous corner king suite that was larger than our first apartment and perfectly decorated, right down to the fantastic towels in the enormous bathroom. The restaurant was first-rate, even when compared to the many options...\n\n\nMore', u'We went for a family trip and had a great time. Great location and rooms. We got a suite for everyone to gather in and three other double rooms for a total of eight people. The hotel is a bit on the small side and more intimate. The staff was great, especially Dwayne at the front door.', u'If you are all about sermdern glass buildings, but vice, then go no further. The hotel may not be part of the flashy , but this property shines where it matters most. I am in Hospitality. I work for a high end hotel in Miami, and this property and its staff gets it right! Somehow the Talbott seems to make...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/07/0a/2a/a3/the-talbott-hotel.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1877', 'title': u'Hampton Inn & Suites Chicago - Downtown Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'33 West Illinois St, Chicago, IL 60654', 'review_list': [u"I stay here week after week and I'm never disappointed!\nThe staff goes above and beyond in trying to make you comfortable.\nThe location is central to food and leisure activities!\nManagement is quick to address any concerns that one may have!", u"My husband and I booked the 1 bedroom King Suite for a three-day weekend in Chicago. I contacted the hotel regarding a special arrangement for my husband's birthday. Damian Cantrelle, Guest Experience Ambassador, was extremely helpful. He coordinated a birthday cake which was in our room when we arrived. Wine glasses magically appeared after the hotel staff saw the wine...\n\n\nMore", u"Normally I don't bother submitting reviews of the Hampton Inns that I stay in - they are uniformly - clean, comfortable and relatively inexpensive. This Hampton was a cut above, with way nicer furniture and interior spaces. Also had central (but individually controlled) heat/AC not the typical window unit that is found in many Hamptons. A better than typical Hampton...\n\n\nMore", u'The hotel, staff,our suite,the amenities,etc. were just wonderful.The staff was very friendly and helpful,our suite was so very nice and roomy, and the breakfast was wonderful .All of this at a very bargain price!', u"This is my second business stay with Hampton and I can't say enough good things about this hotel and its staff. I only regret that I have yet had time to enjoy the pool. Maybe on my next visit though. I'll be back again!", u'A very clean and comfortable hotel in a wonderful part of Chicago. The staff was friendly and helpful. I would definitely stay there again. Hampton Inns are a great value and very consistent. This one, however, was much more than I expected.', u'I have stayed in a number of Chicago hotels for work and tourism. While this one may not be the nicest one, it certainly is the best value for your dollar. I have paid twice as much for much less (Hard Rock Chicago comes to mind.)\nThe rooms are clean and recently updated. The indoor pool, hot tub and sauna...\n\n\nMore', u'The staff at the hotel are very friendly. The indoor pool and hot tub were a delight. The complimentary breakfast was ok. My only complaint was the door in the room had a gap that let a lot of light in but we put a towel over it and it was fine.', u'This hotel gets an "A+" on customer satisfaction. I have never seen an ENTIRE staff - from front desk, housekeeping, doorman, food staff, etc., be so "customer-focused"! Excellent service, clean rooms, helpful staff - all so friendly and polite. Great price too. When in Chicago, I highly recommend you stay at this hotel, as it is near Michigan Ave, shopping,...\n\n\nMore', u'Beautiful room with Chicago skyline view. Great for walking to local restaurants,clubs,\nand shopping! Always stay here,when in Chicago! Love the friendly atmosphere in the middle of the big city. Very relaxing after a busy day sightseeing.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/02/3b/9a/9f/hotel-lobby.jpg', 'class': u'3.0'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'6774', 'title': u'The Palmer House Hilton Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'17 East Monroe Street, Box 75845, Chicago, IL 60603', 'review_list': [u"I'd done some internet research in advance of our trip and discovered something very interesting - the chocolate brownie was actually invented in Chicago! Some ladies who lunched asked the chef at the Palmer House Hotel to make them something like a cake that could be taken in a packed lunch and eaten without mess. The hotel is quite rightly...\n\n\nMore", u'We did a family weekend in the city and found this hotel to be very comfortable and beautiful. It was a great location for the activities we were doing, staff made it special for our twins birthday by bringing a brownie for each when we checked in and the whole family enjoyed the pool. Highly recommend!', u"I was received promptly and the Folks at the desk both coming and going where extremely attentive to my needs. They even offered an envelope for the receipt--haven't seen that in years! The Room was excellent.", u'I stayed here recently for a business conference. The hotel lobby and many of the conference rooms are gorgeous. The rooms are mixed - some are very small, most are very noisy (either the train that starts running around 5a or the intersection traffic that goes all night) - windows are NOT insulated. The steak house restaurant is frightfully expensive...\n\n\nMore', u"Great Hugh hotel rooms are not so new but it's ok it is in a good location bar is very nice concierge is very helpful in the hotel you can find Starbucks and some other food shops. From the airport around 20 min it will cost 50$. Need maybe new decoration in rooms.", u'Check-in: As a Diamond member I was very warmly greeted and had no problem with checking-in at 10 am. We were offered an upgrade to the executive floor double room which was huge(in NYC they would call this presidential suite sort of size). The front desk directed us to the executive elevator that only stopped on 1,22,23 floors.\nRoom: Large...\n\n\nMore', u'I stayed at the Palmer House Hilton by way of a work conference in which my entire company was staying in the same, predesignated hotel.\nInstantly upon checking in, not one but two, of my colleagues encountered multiple cockroaches in their room - instantly facilitating a room upgrade for each, given the blatant nature of the health danger.\nAs if...\n\n\nMore', u'This is a grand old hotel right in the heart of Downtown Chicago. It has many shops and fine restaurants. As well as the grand entrance, and a nice bar to relax and watch the gusts checking in. The rooms are exquisite and very comfortable.', u"Enjoyed my 2 night stay in Chi-town with a compact but quaint room. Freshly renovated and well appointed, the hotel has maintained it's history and charm without looking dated.\nThe rooms are small, as in you can't walk around the bed with the closet door open small, so be prepared for that. Size aside, nothing was missing and the bed...\n\n\nMore", u'As a Diamond member of Hilton Hotels, I generally have positive experiences, thus my loyalty. The desk personnel at the Palmer House (Chicago) were the most "officious", rude people I have come in contact with in my 15 years as a Hilton loyalist. Tonight, and for the next 3 nights, I\'m in a Marriott Suites Hotel. I need a break...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/06/af/ae/8a/the-palmer-house-hilton.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1971', 'title': u'Trump International Hotel & Tower Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'401 N. Wabash Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u"My favorite hotel in Chicago. In room Nespresso machine as well as small kitchen and a nicely appointed bathroom along with a comfortable bed and you can order a sachet from the pillow menu. The pool and locker room are attached to the spa and it's possible to have a mini spa experience in the locker room if you are...\n\n\nMore", u"Amazing spacious suite with large bathrooms and very comfortable bed.\nSPA is very good with a nice gym.\nLocation is perfect.\nIt was my first time in Chicago and for sure when I return we will stay at Trump's Tower", u'Very disappointing that we were put on 17 floor very well knowing that there was going to remodeling with ripping up the carpets next morning. we were woken up with the machines outside our door ripping the carpet out and we had to walk out on a sticky floor. one would expect better from TRUMP.\nthe hand shower had water...\n\n\nMore', u'Our room was simply amazing. We stayed in a corner room on the 27M floor. All I can say is this hotel lacks nothing. They have thought of everything you can think of. One of my favorite was the soaker tub...just wow is all I can say. The team at Trump is just wonderful.You will not be disappointed!', u"I stayed here a while back (in June) before I had a tripadvisor account. In light of stays I have had recently at other hotels, I feel compelled to write a review now as I greatly appreciate the STELLAR and unparalleled service & accommodation I received when I stayed at Trump Chicago. It's the small things that make the overall...\n\n\nMore", u'We took our usual Christmas family trip to Chicago and we stayed at the Trump for the 3rd year in a row. Previously we had stayed at the Peninsula for a few years. We are happy we made the change!\nFrom the start, they take great care of my little girl, and treat her so well. From a stuffed animal...\n\n\nMore', u'The Trump has recently started pumping in a "bad" perfume smell through their front door and elevators...... Why? What are you covering up? This is one of my favorite hotels in Chicago with by far the best rooms with the best location, but this is a deal breaker for me and anyone that doesn\'t want to feel like they stepped...\n\n\nMore', u'great gym, great rooms, good location. my favorite hotel in chicago and Ive pretty much stayed at them all. there is a nice rooftop bar and the restaurant is pretty good. Its a short walk to several other restaurants and the main shopping in the area.', u'Having stayed in hotels all over the world including some pretty famous ones like the Peninsula in Hong Kong , my bar is pretty high . This place clears the bar by several feet . Stayed in 1 bed suite with my daughter . Suite = huge - modern - everything works - is comfortable - clean - people are...\n\n\nMore', u'After staying in multiple 5 star Chicago hotels, I can say that the Trump blows them all away. Service was absolutely beyond belief, and the view from the suite was simply unmatched. Do not waste your time at the Waldorf or Peninsula.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/02/21/ee/29/inside-this-four-star.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'3128', 'title': u'Radisson Blu Aqua Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'221 N. Columbus Drive, Chicago, IL 60601', 'review_list': [u'The rooms in this hotel were clean and modern. We had a nice suite with access to the club floor. The lounge was well stocked and they had a nice breakfast in there. We have found the people at the Radisson Blu hotels to be extremely;y knowledgeable and friendly.', u"Had a wonderful stay at the Radisson Blu Aqua Hotel over New Year's weekend. The staff was wonderful and friendly, not like you would expect in a big city hotel. I booked it because of the proximity to new year celebrations, but would definitely return.", u'I am a gold member in Carlson and have stayed numerous times in this hotel, referred several friends and families, and events to this hotel. Unfortunately, for me, this time, when I wanted to make a reservation they closed out the options to book with my points. The club carlson rep. Ray was very professional and was trying to help...\n\n\nMore', u'Likes:\n+ Allowed an early check-in\n+ Nice spacious room on the 12th floor.\n+ Coffee making machine (but only 1 single cup at a time)\n+ Air-con worked just fine\n+ Very friendly staff\n+ Reasonable collection of gym equipment (both cardio & weights)\n+ Complimentary wifi (7.5 Mbps download; 9.96 Mbps upload)\n+ In-room safe\n+ CVS Store...\n\n\nMore', u'The hotel is absolutely clean as a whistle and the staff is so friendly. The rooms are in tip top shape, the foyer when you first walk in makes you feel like royalty and the doormen are personable and very knowledgeable about locations and anything else you may want to ask.', u"The Radisson Blu is definitely a stunning, ultra-modern hotel both outside and inside, backed up by many awards in both aesthetic and environmental design. While I often view a hotel as somewhere to sleep, Chicago in April isn't the best for always being out, and the hotel offered a very cozy retreat, with its sitting areas and fireplaces. The bar...\n\n\nMore", u'I recently stayed at the Radisson Blu in Chicago. The hotel was outstanding from the reservation process through checkin and departure. The hotel staff was overly attentive to ensure everything was ok with my room and my stay. They have a great fitness center, one of the best that I have seen in a city hotel with a basketball court...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/06/bf/49/fd/lobby.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2214', 'title': u'Palomar Chicago, a Kimpton Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'505 North State Street, Chicago, IL 60654', 'review_list': [u'Very nice hotel. Nice bar, ok restaurant. The staff is very helpful and friendly. Like how close it is to Eatily and Nordstrom. It is quite small which is a plus or minus depending on your preferences. The restaurant needs to expand and upgrade the breakfast menu.', u'The hotel is centrally located with a super friendly staff and lovely ambience. 17th floor pool was awesome for the kids!! Staff made great recommendations and were attentive to all requests. You can even request a goldfish to room with you during your stay!! The only downside was the sirens at night (is there a hospital nearby?).', u'My son and I just spent 5 nights in the Palamar and had a very nice time. We needed 2 beds and wanted a quiet room away from the elevators and the ice machines and we were provided w/1501. The room was at the end of the hall and had nice city Views in its floor to ceiling windows. The...\n\n\nMore', u"Came to town for Chicago restaurant week and stayed here for the first time and have to say it was a great experience. From the great staff at the front desk, to a nicely furnished room to the great location on State in the heart of River North, what's not to like. When we checked in the very friendly lady...\n\n\nMore", u'Our family stay was outstanding! Our room was beautiful, the pool was a blast, the restaurant was great, but most of all the staff was simply amazing. Really fantastic customer service! Everyone from the front desk to the front door and the wait staff in the restaurant were the best!\nSpecial shout out to the front desk help who made...\n\n\nMore', u'We stayed for two nights over a weekend, part of a larger group in Chicago for a fundraiser event. Loved everything about our stay. The service was excellent, everyone was so friendly and accommodating. The rooms are spacious, clean, and very nicely decorated. Quite the trendy look. They have a nice "work out" area and a lovely pool on the...\n\n\nMore', u'I travel to Chicago once a month for business and have stayed in at least 10 different hotels. So far, this is my favorite and will be staying here again next month!\nEverything from the accommodating/welcoming/friendly staff, beautiful rooms, cleanliness, oversized king spa bathtubs, roof top terrace, indoor pool, gym, wine hour for guests and the comfy animal print robes...\n\n\nMore', u'My husband and I had a fabulous time at the hotel Palomor. The one thing that sets this hotel apart was how accommodating and kind every one of their staff members was to us. The location was perfect, and the bed very comfortable. The bathroom was a bit dated, but clean.\nI would suggest joining the Kimpton rewards program. We...\n\n\nMore', u"We stayed at the Palomar for a quick weekend stay in Chicago to see the Blackhawks game. We loved this hotel and would definitely stay there again. We had the artists suite, which was their largest suite according to the very nice girl who'd checked us in upon arrival. Very spacious one bedroom, 1 1/2 bath suite, perfect for our...\n\n\nMore", u'We stayed for a long weekend and the 1br suite was well worth the money! Great spa bathroom and space, service and of course the free happy hour for kids and adults. Rooftop pool was fun and mostly vacant in the middle if the day, great for kids at 3.5 ft deep.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/08/bf/75/77/palomar-chicago-a-kimpton.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2537', 'title': u'Omni Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'676 North Michigan Ave, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'Guest rooms are very clean. The Hotel staff is friendly and very helpful. Meeting rooms, bar, lobby are all above average. It was so nice coming back to room with peaceful music playing . Food was good and staff is very attentive to food allergies. Very typical Omni service.', u"Staff is incredible; they truly understand going above and beyond; from surprising my kids with cookies and milk, to great recommendations, directions and literally walking me to my car. I've traveled the world and this was the best experience I've had in a hotel or resort.", u"Our stay at the Omni for my granddaughter and myself for the Amnerican Girl Doll package was beyond amazing. The staff, hotel and accomadations couldn't be better. I highly recommend staying at the Omni Hotel. The location was great, with everything being at your fingertips. Great price for such a beautiful hotel.", u"This hotel and it's staff are exceptiona, hospitable, friendly, accomodating and professional. The rooms are very nice and comfortable and clean. I usually do not like to eat in hotels, but the restaurant is very good with beautiful views and excellent service. The location of the hotel is also great! I will always stay at this Omni while in Chicago...highly...\n\n\nMore", u'We stayed at the Omni for a quick weekend in Chicago to see a show. The hotel is nicely appointed, staff and rooms are good and prices are in keeping with the area and type of hotel. The location is great for accessing the "Miracle Mile" and other parts of Chicago. We would stay there again.', u'Celebrated my 35th Birthday Jan 16th. The customer service was amazing from the time of arrival to the time of departure. They had a piece of chocolate cake with happy birthday on the serving dish and complementary champagnes my suite. The views from the room were amazing. So the next morning I went downstairs to my buddies room to watch...\n\n\nMore', u"When I walked in, person checking me in didn't look up once and to be honest treated me like I was beneath him. Hotel is nice. Amenities are great. Beautiful, spacious rooms. I attended the bar that night and drink selection was great and food was well prepared and yummy. Because of my check-in treatment, I wouldn't stay here again.", u'we stayed at the omni for two nights in december while shopping, eating and having a few cocktails. great location and nice hotel....nice service....convenient\nWell Done Omni! I flew into Midway...,not a bad taxi ride.\nLobby area and bar are very comfortable and inviting.', u"I can't praise this hotel enough. Quick check in. Helpful staff in every way. Clean, large room with great ability to both work and relax. Complimentary coffee service to my room as a standard club member.\nthank you Chicago Omni", u'Great experience; staff is excellent; hotel is excellent; great location; would recommend hotel to others; Stayed on business - would come back for personal stay. Valet parking is expensive though. Did not eat at any of the restaurants in the hotel.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/08/6a/69/65/hotel-entrance.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2007', 'title': u'Hotel Monaco Chicago - a Kimpton Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'225 N Wabash, Chicago, IL 60601', 'review_list': [u'My boyfriend and I enjoyed our 3 night stay at Hotel Monaco. The staff were all very pleasant- especially the doormen- all super helpful and just really nice to talk to! The bed was very comfortable and we were able to get a good nights sleep all three nights. The hotel also provided beverages throughout the day, which was nice...\n\n\nMore', u'Our room was large and very clean. The bed was very comfortable and the hotel was very quiet for sleeping. Close to Chicago River and very scenic at night. Staff was cordial and helpful when asked for advice', u'Stayed at the Monaco for an Anniversary weekend. Enjoyed every minute of our stay! Very clean hotel, friendly staff, decent sized rooms for downtown Chicago. Had a River View room and the views of the river and surrounding buildings were awesome, especially at night. Enjoyed the window seat as well! Also the wine reception was nice although it was very...\n\n\nMore', u'The Hotel Monaco was the perfect location for our overnight birthday celebration. It put us within walking distance of everything we had planned. Great eclectic design throughout the lobby and rooms. We had a fifth floor room with a north view and it was amazing to sit on the window bench and just watch the city go by. The room...\n\n\nMore', u"I've stayed at Hotel Monaco on numerous visits to Chicago. The staff are great, even arranging for my coat to be sent up to my hotel in Milwaukee free of charge when I left in Chicago. The rooms are spacious and comfortable, free wine in an evening and a great restaurant for breakfast. Centrally located and within walking distance of...\n\n\nMore", u"I can't say enough good things about this hotel. First, the staff was friendly and helpful with excellent restaurant recommendations, directions and help printing airline tickets, not to mention their kind and friendly greetings. Next, the room was very clean and roomy with a great view of the river and Trump tower which my teenage daughter found hilarious. The location...\n\n\nMore", u'Hotel Monoco proved to be a top notch place to stay. The location was perfect, no taxi rides required. We had shopping to do in Water Tower to the north, dinner to the west, and theater tickets to the south, all blocks away. The facility was very stylish, clean, well appointed and the staff attentive and eager to please. I...\n\n\nMore', u'This cozy boutique hotel is located just south of the river near the loop in downtown Chicago, Illinois. Extremely friendly staff. Snagged a great rate for $125 a night in a Mediterranean Suite. The high floors offer nice views of downtown Chicago. Wine reception between 5 and 6 in the afternoon. Very friendly atmosphere. Very dog friendly. Within easy walking...\n\n\nMore', u'Hotels.Com strikes again. Found this cool hotel just by chance. Boutique like with very comfortable rooms. Coffee and infused water in the lobby where we sat by the fireplace to read the newspaper. Service was excellent.', u"I wanted a break from the usual bland international hotels and this one appeared to fit the bill. I was not disappointed. Clean, friendly, quiet and charmingly decorated. I'm already booked in for my next visit."], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/09/8c/9b/f2/cmndeluxe-room-bathroom.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1105', 'title': u'Thompson Chicago, a Thompson Hotel', 'rating_string': u'5.0', 'address': u'21 E. Bellevue Place, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u"We stayed at the Thompson for the first time and found it to be quite pleasant and enjoyable. The door and desk staff are amazing in their service and friendliness. We had a dinner in the hotel restaurant and our waitress was very accommodating of my wife's food sensitivities. The food was fantastic! We have stayed at other Chicago hotels...\n\n\nMore", u"After arriving, I received a survey email asking me about my checkin experience. Excellent. There was room for a comment, and I said that being from Texas where the air wasn't so dry, I hadn't thought to pack lotion. Within minutes, I received an email saying lotion would be brought up immediately. Then I received a phone call asking if...\n\n\nMore", u"My husband and I spent a few days after New Year's here. Our first night, as we got in late, meant we just ate and drank at the hotel bar. It was probably the best meal and cocktails of the whole trip! The bartenders really know their stuff, and try the awesome sweet potato pasta dish.\nThe staff and service...\n\n\nMore", u'Stayed there for one night. Hotel was beautiful, and the location of the hotel is excellent as it is within walking distance to Magnificent Mile and restaurants. They have complimentary car service from 5PM-9PM on a first come, first serve basis. Staff was extremely friendly. Used the fitness facility which was nice.', u'I stayed at The Thompson in October of 2015 with my best friend for a weekend getaway. From the moment we walked in, we knew this was going to be an absolutely exceptional hotel. Management has gone out of their way to make every detail as memorable as possible - from the way the hotel lobby smells, to the quaint...\n\n\nMore', u'This hotel is beautiful, in a great location and has great service. The rooms are airy and well lit, have great, modern, interior design and the hotel manages to pull off cool and stylish without seeming stuck up.\nThe only complaint i have is one of the elevators was closed the entire time of my stay and by talking to...\n\n\nMore', u"The Thompson Hotel is truly 5 Star. Ultra Modern Styling and Luxury at it's best. The Thompson is located between the Michigan Ave. Gold Coast and Rush Street action with shopping,nightclubs and fine dining. Large nicely appointed rooms with all the comforts and amenities. There's a small lobby bar in the hotel or choose from a number of trendy night...\n\n\nMore", u'Loved the Thompson. It was in an awesome location...easy walking to everywhere. Good size rooms, even with 4 of us. Lots of great places to eat close by. Very Modern and clean rooms, with big bathrooms, and cool decor in the foyer with a groovy bar and restaurant. Not many extras though. No WiFi, no fridge, no in room coffee...\n\n\nMore', u'Our family of 5, adults and young adult daughters stayed at the Thompson for 4 nights in January. We loved this hotel, its centrally located just of the mag mile. Within walking distance but slightly removed which was nice. We had a lake view room which was amazing. The bar was a great place to people watch each night and...\n\n\nMore', u'From check in to check out the service was 5 star.\nRoom was spacious, as well as a beautiful modern bathroom.\nLobby and adjacent facilities were comfortable, well decorated and trendy.\nStaff was attentive, courteous and helpful.\nWill definitely return.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/04/a8/cb/fb/thompson-chicago.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'4788', 'title': u'Hyatt Regency Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'151 East Wacker Drive, Chicago, IL 60601', 'review_list': [u'The hotel was clean, comfortable and situated nicely to the shopping but so are 95% of the places in Chicago. Some of the staff was snippy at times. The Bellman kept flashing the cash in his hand as to say, tip me. The room next to ours was so loud and rowdy we were awakened at 3 AM and had...\n\n\nMore', u'Stayed at the hotel for a trade show. The lobby was grand and beautiful, the staff was friendly and the room was very clean. Unfortunately I had an ice cold shower one morning and my television was broken. I would stay here again, and recommend, but I was slightly disappointed with the cold shower. :/', u'My son and I stayed here for 3 nights in January 2016 to visit Northwestern. The hotel is located within easy walking distance of the Art Institute and the other central destinations. Our room was clean and well-appointed. Our only real complaint is that the cable TV cuts out a lot. We also made the mistake of eating some candy...\n\n\nMore', u'We enjoy bringing the family to this centrally located hotel...close walk to everything. Rooms are nice and service is great. Food is good too! Cabs are always around too if you need them which is important.', u'The Hyatt Regency, located near the corner of Michigan avenue and North Wacker Drive, is ideally located downtown within a 20 minute walk from most major attractions and nightlife. The hotel itself is updated with plenty of amenities both on premises or through underground shopping areas.\nTravel to and from the airports is also easy using the "L". Take the...\n\n\nMore', u'Located about a block from Michigan Ave., across from the Chicago River, its location is great and makes a lot accessible by walking or renting a bike or even public transit!\nHotel is big, which is also the name of the bar situation near the entrance of the hotel. Check in is located at the top of a stair well/escalator...\n\n\nMore', u"I'm a long time Hyatt club member and have been disappointed of late with some of their Hyatt's around the country however the Hyatt Regency in Chicago was a real pleasant surprise! It's in great condition even in the middle of winter.\nThe main lobby and guest reception areas are clean, modern, comfortable and spacious. Plenty of room to make...\n\n\nMore", u'Nice hotel, excellent front desk staff. It is located in a great spot in Chicago, close to many attractions. We had an excellent experience at this hotel. I would recommend this hotel if visiting Chicago to be close to lots of activities. Safe location and nearby public transportation for travel to attractions.', u'Great location and nice accommodations! Great restaurants and bar on location. You can walk to any tourist attraction. Our room had views of the river,and the lake was only a couple of blocks away. The room was clean and met our needs.', u'We stayed here for one night before flying out for our cruise. Check in was fast and friendly. Our room was clean and comfortable. We used the park and fly and it was all very convenient. The one set back, was on our shuttle back to the hotel from airport, we had to make two stops and it took quite...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-fw/05/84/fc/03/lobby--v885210-81.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'841', 'title': u'Warwick Allerton Hotel Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'701 N. Michigan Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611 (Formerly Allerton Hotel)', 'review_list': [u"This is a great hotel if your looking to be in the middle of a great shopping area. Be aware that free in-room wifi isn't available but the staff are very friendly. The hotel has a great vibe and I would consider staying here again.", u"Don't eat breakfast at the in hotel restaurant. $15 for a sausage mushroom, cheese omelet. $2.50 for coffee when it is free in the next room. And orange juice is portrayed as free, is definitely not free. Internet is $10 a day, so have a back up plan. And most annoying, no refrigerator. Where am I going to put my...\n\n\nMore", u'Michigan Avenue = spending money. Staying at The Allerton Hotel = saves valuable cash for more shopping, dining and attractions. This property serves the savvy traveler well - it is relatively inexpensive and provides comfortable rooms for sleeping. While not luxury, The Allerton is a good base camp and has a hint of Gold Coast style. Best at a promotional...\n\n\nMore', u'Very old hotel, very cold bathrooms with wallpaper coming down. The maids were not very nice. We were given mean looks by them and receiving a knock on your door at 820 am so they can come in and clean is not good.', u'We had reserved thrue Expedia with a non refundable rate. Unfortunately our flight was cancelled so we ended up staying for one less night. The hotel was very accomadating by refunding us for that night.\nStaff was friendly and room was clean. Yes it was a bit noisy but not uncommon for a building of that age.\nReading thrue the...\n\n\nMore', u'The staff were super friendly and the building is phenomenally beautiful. It was a great stay and made my Chicago visit comfortable. The room service were expeditious, and the room service was competent.', u"The room was tiny and basic with no amenities except the television. There wasn't even a coffee maker. But considering the location it was very cheap, so I have no complaints. I wish the check-in staff were a little friendlier. But overall, it was adequate. The location really makes up for all these.", u'Great place to stay, great location in town, near all the big shops, just 5-10 min walk to the best dish pizza places and just minutes from skyDeck. Hotel room, bathroom, sheets and space and d\xe9cor worth the cost. We highly recommend it.', u"We stayed here for a quick trip to Chicago before going out to the suburbs for a wedding. The location was great and our only complaint was how tiny the hotel room was. If you don't mind that, this location was great and the price of the hotel was a total steal. Definitely recommend this if it is just one...\n\n\nMore", u'The Staff was very slow,Also the hotel does not have microwave.The bathroom toilet look like if it was from a bathroom stall from out of a restaurant. Bathroom supposed to be a home feeling. Also 2 light bulbs did not work, have to call front desk to ask for batteries for the remote control.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/06/d0/46/d6/historical-landmark-hotel.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'3301', 'title': u'Wyndham Grand Chicago Riverfront Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'71 East Wacker Drive, Chicago, IL 60601', 'review_list': [u'Shades of brown/beige decor (very 80s) and could do with a refurb, but rooms were clean and comfy, hotel staff were fine, good value for a location on the southern edge of the Mag Mile a short walk from the El', u'Okay so to start reception was lovely they even upgraded my room to river front which was really nice of them. This review is in no way negative to any staff just the hotel itself. My room was amazing bathroom bedroom great! It looked like a new refurbished room. The hotel itself was really noisy. The doors to the rooms...\n\n\nMore', u'The check-in was very smooth and room is large. It started nice but is developing to a disaster. The hotel has apparently big problems with Wi-Fi. I spent two days with their support on the phone. At the beggining they said it was my laptop, then they promised to fix it but Wi-Fi never worked. The third day finally someone...\n\n\nMore', u'Was in Chicago for work and stayed at the Wyndham. What an awesome experience it was. The hotel staff goes above and beyond when it comes to service, especially Anthony at the front desk. I needed to stay an extra couple nights and he made it incredibly easy & affordable!', u'We stayed at The Wyndham Grand to be in the heart of downtown Chicago. It was close to everything and a very enjoyable stay. I would recommend this hotel,definitely a wonderful stay!We could easily walk to Michigan Avenue too.', u'This was a trip with 4 women in their mid-late 20s.\nThe good:\n1. The location was great. One of the women had never been to CHI before and one had been once when she was very young. The location was right in between all the touristy stuff (the Mile north of us; Grant Park and Theatre District south of...\n\n\nMore', u'Amazing deal for amazing hotel! Close to river and all shopping spots. Such a great place without breaking the bank. Saved money to be able to waste at all the shops! haha. Wyndham hotels never disappoint.', u'Our stay was above and beyond our expectations. The manager was so helpful and kind along with the rest of the staff. The view from our room window was amazing, looking out at the river and trump tower. Definitely plan on staying and the Wyndham Grand again when I visit the city.', u'Spent a birthday weekend with friends. Perfect location for everyone coming in from different cities. Rooms were clean and nice. Not the quietest hotel, could here people talking in hallways and other rooms.\nStaff in Hoyts Tavern were friendly.\nMark Zematis, the bell/door man was attentive and helpful. Always met us with a smile.\nWill definitely stay here again.', u'Room was spacious, bathroom had two sinks which was great for us! A keurig! And very, very comfy beds. The staff was very accommodating and there is a Starbucks in the bar downstairs.....very handy!\nWould definately pick this again......on the river, close to the train to Michigan City and they stored our stuff for free while we shopped!'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/06/8b/8b/1d/wyndham-grand-chicago.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1921', 'title': u'Four Seasons Hotel Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'120 E. Delaware Pl., Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u"We have visited the Four Seasons so often that we feel like it's an extension of home.\nOur first evening - Friday night - we met about 20 friends down in the lobby lounge, essentially throwing ourselves a private party in the evening. Service was great and everyone had a blast.\nIn the rooms, chocolate milk is delivered to the...\n\n\nMore", u'We stayed here for a conference for work and absolutely loved it! First thank you to the staff - they work so hard to ensure your experience is perfect. The rooms are big and beautiful and immaculate. The location is perfectly situated in downtown Chicago close to everything, including shopping. It will be hard to stay at other hotels now...\n\n\nMore', u"Good hotel, with great customer service. Was cold in winter, and staff would wait outside for cabs/limo's, and then come get guests that were waiting inside. Did not eat in restaurant. Great gym. Good sleep on a firm bed.", u'I previously reviewed the Four Seasons Chicago, and we loved this hotel. We stay here often, and have loved it over the years. However, we recently stayed in December and had a horrible experience that made me question the safety of this hotel. At around 3 am we were awakened by a garbled announcement from the Chicago fire department advising...\n\n\nMore', u"I've been here three times and I love this place. From the door man to the taste of the coffee just delivered to my hotel room, this place does it right. The lobby is perhaps my favorite lobby in a city hotel (vs an open air lobby in a resort) in all the land - the art, the clean look...\n\n\nMore", u'Just when you think that there is no hope, that America is circling the drain, that we are on the road to anarchy and self-destruction, out of the abyss of despair rises The Phoenix of hope! Certainly a few days at the Four Seasons in Chicago will do this. My gosh, what a hotel! A corner suite with a wrap...\n\n\nMore', u'I am late in writing this review as I stayed in the start of December, but it was one of the best stays I have ever had at a hotel. We got early check in when we arrived which was great and the Bellhop told me where to get some famous Chicago pizza. Sydney at check in was so kind...\n\n\nMore', u'This was the 4th Four Seasons property we have been lucky enough to stay in around the world. When you pay the extra for this name you tend to expect the best.\nI am happy to report that the Four Seasons Chicago didnt disappoint.\nFrom check in to check out they were soooooo helpful. What i love is that ALL...\n\n\nMore', u"We stayed at the Four Seasons to celebrate my mother-in-laws birthday. The room was spectacular with beautiful views of the city. The bath room was spacious and great attention to detail. It's a great location for shopping, eating and walks on the lake. The staff all made us feel welcome and at home. Can't wait to return in the Spring.", u"Spent the night at the Four Season along with massages for my wife and myself at the spa. The men's locker room was messy, the steam and the sauna were of the quality I would expect from a park district...run down and old. The spa had a general waiting room that was like Union Station - do not expect to...\n\n\nMore"], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/c3/72/7a/deluxe-king.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1645', 'title': u'Silversmith Hotel Chicago Downtown', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'10 S Wabash Ave, Chicago, IL 60603 (Formerly The Silversmith Hotel)', 'review_list': [u'Was there for 11 nights for work. When I checked in, I asked for the quietest room possible - and aside from minimal noise from the L on Wabash, which is unavoidable - James at the front desk was able to honor my request with a 10th floor/top floor room, away from the elevators, and away from the street. I...\n\n\nMore', u'We stayed at the Silversmith for one night during the week. We were in town for a broadway show. The location was perfect for walking to the theater and shopping. The hotel was clean and the staff was very helpful and friendly. The current construction going on in front of the hotel caused us a little delay in getting to...\n\n\nMore', u'Myself and my husband stayed in the Silversmith for 5 nights over New Year. The hotel staff were always friendly and helpful. The location was perfect, right near trains and easy walking distance to main sights. The room was a good size and very stylish and clean! The price was great for the standard of the hotel and location. I...\n\n\nMore', u'The Silversmith is one of the most elegant hotels in Chicago. The location is perfect and the rooms are breathtaking. They are so spacious and the be is super comfortable. I will not stay anywhere else when I visit Chicago!', u'This hotel room was quite spacious and very nice! I was very happy with how much space we had for our kingsize bedroom. I also liked the silver decor. Very romantic stay here! I would have liked to get a room with a view but was quite pleased with the price we paid and the room we received.', u'This was our stay at the Silversmith. The location is excellent for attending a dinner and play. It is only a short walk to the theaters. The bed was extremely comfortable and one of the best hotel beds that I have slept in. We will return to the Silversmith!', u'We used to live in Chicago, and came back for a weekend getaway without our kids. From the moment we walked in we were treated well: the staff at the front desk are warm and welcoming, check in was fast and painless and then we were walking in to our room on the 10th floor, which was a)ENORMOUS compared to...\n\n\nMore', u'Perfect location in the loop area of chicago. Close to the Millennium park. Very nice boutique hotel with a great small restaurant for breakfast. Room are large and designed with a European touch......', u'Fantastic location in downtown, walking distance to most attractions. Area felt very safe even late at night, decent amount of restaurants and shopping nearby for breakfast and late dinners. Room is very clean, modern d\xe9cor and spacious. Bed was a bit too high, but otherwise very comfortable.', u"the -best from The moment we got there till the end of our visit the people who work in the hotel making you feel like home and take care for you very well anything you need and you just ask , it's a great location in down town ,clean, Great service! \u2764\U0001f3d9\U0001f44dcoming in the summer for sure \u2708\ufe0f"], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/05/94/14/97/the-silversmith-hotel.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1287', 'title': u'Hyatt Chicago Magnificent Mile Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'633 North Saint Clair Street, Chicago, IL 60611 (Formerly Wyndham Chicago)', 'review_list': [u'If I could pull a dumpster out off my rear and then with everything in it, build a hotel; this would be the result. This is the truest example of lipstick on a pig.. Everything looks nice but the staff is rude and unhelpful, unapologetic, and straight up lazy. There is only one parking option which is $60 US after...\n\n\nMore', u'Stayed one night recently for business. Check in was fast and easy, our room was ready when we arrived at 11:00am. Received a high floor room as requested. Room was nice, king bed was comfortable. TV had plenty of channels. Pool area and gym area were very clean and neat. Only pool area issue we noted was the hot tub....\n\n\nMore', u'Well its close to shopping and the botique hotel location is one of the prime benefits of this hotel and the suite rooms offer a great space for work and plan and the HVAC system is quiet and that means easy cleep and rest and work. We stay at hyatt hotels up to 3 months at a time and we...\n\n\nMore', u'I have styed here two times for business. Great location that is within walking distance to everything I need/want to do downtown. The room service is prompt and the food is great! Super clean and friendly. I will stay here again for sure. Wifi is fast and easy to use as well. Only negative is that the location is near...\n\n\nMore', u'The title of the review pretty much says it. It is exactly what you would expect. I have stayed here at least once a year for the last five or six years. It is consistent and good, without being exceptional. If you travel a lot, this will be a comforting experience, in that you could be anywhere. The rooms do...\n\n\nMore', u'We took the kids to the city for a long weekend and were very pleased with Hyatt Chicago. Definitely book the Executive Suite with the kids, lots of room and nice area to relax. Pool could have been larger but kids still enjoyed it.', u'Great location, amenities, and service! Nice, boutique feel to it but with the service level expected of Hyatt. I love staying here when in Chicago. Great bar with local beer choices, and some interesting cocktails. Fantastic breakfast and room service. Concierge, Bell Staff, and Front Desk very helpful about local transportation, activities, and dining options.', u'It was a very nice hotel and well located for our purpose. The staff were friendly and the room in excellent condition. A great hospitality experience and a great price at this time of year. I especially like the fact that Hyatt properties are always well-appointed and consistent.', u"Stayed here for a hospital visit. Northwestern Hospital Galter Pavilion is across the street. Women's and Children's hospitals are another block, but close. Choose a high floor, due to sirens, though honestly they weren't bad. I was on the tenth floor.", u'This is a renovated large hotel in the heart of the Chicago Mag Mile area. It is perfectly located to access all of the Northwestern Medical Complex buildings as well as the dining and shopping in the area. It is on the corner of Michigan Avenue, right at the heart of the action and a couple of blocks from Rush...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/04/56/74/e3/king-guest-room.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'3204', 'title': u'InterContinental Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'505 North Michigan Ave, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'Things I really liked:\n- blazing in-room wifi\n- location is pefect, you can walk anywhere in River North or the Loop in 20 minutes or less\n- gift of a bottle of Domaine Chandon (it was our anniversary - thank you)\nA couple of tips:\n- closest place to buy water/snacks/beer is the 7-11 two blocks north on Ohio,...\n\n\nMore', u"Good gym/swimming facilities, just a shame they were unmanned when I visited. I'm not sure if this is normal or just the two times I visited (once early morning, the other in the evening). Room was good with tons of room, bed very comfortable. Next time I'm in Chicago I'll be coming back and staying here again.", u'Stayed here in January 2016. Service was very good from the first minute on. Room was big and spacious, I need to give special credit to bed in my room, I was sleeping better than for a long time. Hotel is also centrally located, so everything was easy to reach by foot also.', u"We arrived in Chicago by car and needed a place to stay the night before catching a flight out of O'Hara the next day. We stayed at this hotel a year earlier and were pleased to find room availability since we enjoyed our first stay so much! The rooms were clean, comfortable and very well appointed, The pool is in...\n\n\nMore", u'I booked this hotel partly to see what it was like and also because I got a good deal on the room. Check-in was a breeze and I quickly realized as I rode up to my room in the elevator why this hotel was so popular. The family who joined me seemed rich in a nonchalant way. I was somewhat...\n\n\nMore', u"As soon as I arrived at the intercontinental every need and want was attended to. Easy check-in and beautiful accommodations. The original tower in this hotel used to be a prestigious men's club back in the 1920s, then much later they added another tower. The original portion of the hotel is breathtaking in its design and interior, carefully restored. The...\n\n\nMore", u'I been on the IHG/Hilton fence for years. I wish I could pick one because I would benefit from the combined loyalty. IHG is tempting me with what may be may favorite US hotel. Writing that is almost like admitting I have fallen in love. This is only my second stay at the InterContinental Chicago. I wrote a stellar review...\n\n\nMore', u'The InterContinental Chicago is centrally located on Michigan Avenue beside the Chicago Tribune building and opposite the Wrigley building and Nordstrom \u2013 my suite had stunning views of many of Chicago\u2019s landmark buildings, the ones mentioned, as well as Sears Tower. This is a great location with loads of great restaurants, bars, shopping and local sites. I love architecture and...\n\n\nMore', u"Great location, great views, great service. We were treated extremely well, the rooms are 5 stars, and you are minutes away from all the major attractions, plus you can walk in the great Magnificient Mile. Don't forget to take your swimsuit, even in winter, they have a beautiful indoor pool from the 1920's. Excellent choice!!", u'The Intercontinental Chicago is located just north of the river on Michigan Avenue. This is the prime scene in Chicago, and the location towards the southern end of Magnificent Mile actually provides a benefit because it is also walkable to any part of the Loop. We found this useful during our stay.\nDue to a change in itinerary, we had...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-p/0a/29/c6/46/exterior-entrance-michigan.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1829', 'title': u'ACME Hotel Company Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'15 East Ohio Street, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'This is the second time my girl friend and I have stayed at the Acme and we love it! Nice sized rooms, super clean, easy parking, down town, awesome bar, it is everything you could hope for in a down town hotel.', u'Stayed at the Acme because I was meeting up with some friends from college that were visiting. The hotel and Staff were awesome and the room was spotless and had a very comfy bed. It was within walking distance to some awesome bars, we had a blast. Thanks Acme for an awesome visit. Will definitely be back!', u'This hotel is so awesome. Hard to actually explain how amazing my room was. It had two separate rooms. Everything you need or expect from a hotel room was in this room. The decor is super cute. Love the bathroom mirror. The shower head is cool also! I highly recommend this hotel! Its just great in every way possible!', u"The day before we arrived, I received an email about checking in online. We weren't arriving until late (around 10:30pm) the next night so I figured checking in online would save a minute. I was emailed within a half hour of checking in online saying that my room (1501) was all ready! I emailed the front desk and ordered coffee...\n\n\nMore", u"The room was clean, the location is perfect and the value was amazing. My tiny problem was, early check in. I called the day before my arrival and was told I can check in early, but that didn't happen. I was told the hotel sold out the night before and every room was busy. They promised to call me as...\n\n\nMore", u'My husband and I have stayed here numerous times and keep coming back. It is affordable, clean and has a great location. It also has a club on the main level and an excellent bakery. Parking at $39 is also affordable for downtown Chicago. We love it here.', u'This place is Awesome. Great location and amenities. If requested, they will deliver fresh coffee to you every morning from the first floor bakery. The bakery also had amazing bacon and egg croissants. Cool bar also located inside hotel. Great for pregame or night cap.', u"Stayed for one night in ACME's suite room with an amazing city view! The front desk service was very welcoming and knowledgable, the room was trendy and comfortable and the Knock & Drop service was a great perk in the morning. ACME is unlike any other hotel I've ever stayed in. Highly recommend the ACME Hotel during your time in...\n\n\nMore", u'Last minute anniversary trip and decided to check out the Acme. A very pleasant surprise. A few very minor issues, but the positives very much outweighed the few imperfections. I will definitely book here again. Friendly staff and nice lounge a bonus.', u"First visit was for a me weekend for Mother's Day last year. Acme Hotel made it wonderful. This time it was a family experience. The rooms were great, especially the rain showers and Lather products. This rockin' chick will be back!"], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-p/04/4e/83/92/acme-hotel-company-chicago.jpg', 'class': u'3.0'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2071', 'title': u'Kinzie Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'20 W Kinzie St, Chicago, IL 60654 (Formerly Amalfi Hotel Chicago)', 'review_list': [u"We stayed here one night just to hangout downtown. We used a Groupon and got a good price. I don't know that paying the extra money for a Deluxe City View King room was worth it though for 2 reasons: 1. The hotel isn't that tall so your view in general is nothing to write home about 2. We didn't...\n\n\nMore", u'We stayed 4 nights in this hotel.\nThe room was big, comfortable and clean.\nThe continental breakfast was included. It was a self service on every floor in front of the elevator. You have to put what you want on your tray and then come back to the room for enjoy breakfast.\nThe location is the best thing. The hotel...\n\n\nMore', u'AS the title says this hotel was great.Great front desk and doormen, always greeting us with a hello and a smile. The evening reception staff was also great. The breakfast was fine, but.....3 of the 4 mornings we did not have breakfast on our floor as advertised as one of the amenities at the Kinzie. Because of "low occupancy" on...\n\n\nMore', u'I had a wonderful experience at the Kinzie Hotel in Chicago. All members of the hotel staff were courteous and helpful. Melissa Driza, the Guest Services Manager and Chief Concierge, provided exceptional customer service. I enjoyed the complimentary Continental Breakfast offered everyday,as well as the Lounge located on the 5th floor. The Kinzie Hotel is located in a very convenient...\n\n\nMore', u"I use this hotel for my boss' travel to Chicago, which is frequent, as my first choice for her travels. If I have any revisions to dates, etc., the in-house customer service team is always accommodating and friendly. I just worked with Kevin to revise a date to earlier in the week and he actually got me a lower rate...\n\n\nMore", u'Stayed here for 3 nights in Nov. Even though the name changed to Kinzie, it is still pretty much the same. The rooms are spacious and clean. There is breakfast every morning near the elevator on each floor. There is also a nightly happy hour with cocktails and light appetizers. The location is perfect. It is in River North near...\n\n\nMore', u"This is a great hotel in a prime location in Chicago. The weather was not so cold so I was able to walk everywhere. Rate includes continental breakfast, which is set up on each floor outside the elevators, for your convenience as they don't have an on-site restaurant. Although it was kind of basic (continental after all), it was plentiful...\n\n\nMore", u'My wife and I stayed at the Kinzie for 3 nights over new years. The amazing customer service began the moment we arrived at the hotel. The doorman Khan was quite helpful with our baggage and ushering us into check-in.\nWe arrived early, but luckily we were helped by the customer service manager Melissa. Not only did we get an...\n\n\nMore', u'Stayed here for a mini vacation with my fianc\xe9 and we had a blast. This hotel is in the perfect location! We took the L from Midway to State/Lake and the hotel is only a 4 block walk away from that stop. There are plenty of restaurants and cool bars in the surrounding blocks too. Hotel staff was extremely friendly....\n\n\nMore', u'This a great hotel, with great customer service. The rooms were very clean and beds comfortable.\nPerhaps the best part is that a VERY good breakfast is served at every floor. You take a tray from your room, walk down the hall, get your food and enjoy it in your room.\nThe treadmills were great for when I wanted to...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-p/05/4b/24/6b/amalfi-hotel-chicago.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'725', 'title': u'W Chicago Lakeshore Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'644 N Lake Shore Dr, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'As soon as we arrived, there were people out there to greet us. Great first impression. Even when I went out for food and came back at 2 in the morning there was a nice doorman who made sure all of my needs were met! Besides that, the trip was not so amazing. My family and I were waiting for...\n\n\nMore', u'We had a social event a the hotel and everyone was servicing us with such excellent and attentive customer service. From the pre planning, tasting to the day of the event from valet to banquets every thing went flawless. The staff went out of their way to make everything look at taste great! I would highly recommend this hotel for...\n\n\nMore', u'I can\'t say enough about my stay at this location. I flew in for a job interview. The staff was efficient is getting me checked-in and reminded me of all of the amenities available to me during my brief stay. Whenever I walked past the desk, someone was there to say, "hello." The room was fantastic and smelled so good--none...\n\n\nMore', u'We threw a party for about 150 a the W Lakeshore last weekend. It was a wonderful and seamless experience. The staff was so accommodating and friendly. Brittney Carter was so easy to work with and responsive. The food was out of this world, both for the dinner as well as the brunch the next day. The catering chef was...\n\n\nMore', u'Loved this hotel! The rooms were clean and updated, plus the staff were very friendly. The views of the lake were awesome and this was a great location - we were able to walk everywhere. Only downside was that it cost about $20 for a beer in the lobby.', u'Hotel was very clean, and staff was very pleasant to deal with. Wonderful location with lake views. I would recommend this hotel to anyone who asks. This hotel was within walking distance to many bars and restaurants.', u'I came here for an overnight stay with my wife and in-laws. I booked the room through priceline and immediately ran into troubles trying to speak with the hotel staff to ensure that I would have separate beds in the room. I called customer service and the woman that I spoke with was extremely dismissive and unhelpful. She said nothing...\n\n\nMore', u"Our stay was more than expected . Beautiful view, frozen over lake and all. Hanna the front desk receptionist was excellent, very nice and welcoming.\nI recommend the higher floor ( 30 ) close to the elevator ... The bar area was nice and open.\nWe had regular check out at noon , next time we'll do late check out....\n\n\nMore", u"Stayed here for 4 nights for a company meeting. The rooms were great. Great view of the lake (albeit frozen). Meeting space was excellent (33rd floor). The food was above average. We got a good group rate. Location is great for some things, but there isn't a lot of nightlife within walking distance on a cold night like there is...\n\n\nMore", u'Lyndsay went out of her way to help start my day out right. (After hours coffee) The views are awesome at the W not to mention the hotel is up to date and clean. ***** without question this is 5 stars ***** I would visit this hotel again and again. Close to everything you could want or need.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/06/17/0b/b1/w-chicago-lakeshore.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2302', 'title': u'dana hotel and spa, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'660 North State Street, Chicago, IL 60654', 'review_list': [u'The hotel was beautiful. Staff was so friendly and helpful. The decor is very sophisticated and modern. I would stay there again. Location was not bad if you plan to shop the Millennium Mile. Do not stay on top floor though. Bar/club is on the roof, which is cool if you are on a lower floor.', u'There was so much hair in the shower that I thought an animal was crawling out of the drain, the extra pillow was put into the closet without the case being changed from the previous guest, smelled of old lady perfume and of course hairy... gross ! it was needed because the pillows were completely flat, the bed was more...\n\n\nMore', u'Friendly Staff, well appointed room, in the heart of downtown. There are numerous restaurants and shopping within easy walking distance. The city skyline views are awesome. Will definitely stay here again.', u"I've loved this hotel in the past and was excited to return for a long weekend in Chicago. The location is terrific and I like their spa quite a lot. a) my room was small -- which is fine -- but I was a bit surprised at a lack of window! There was only a small door to the outside...\n\n\nMore", u'a modern hotel with smart and well equipped rooms. An excellent spa and all topped off with a marvellous roof top bar that welcomed the slightly older client like myself as well as the bright young things of Chicago. Very friendly staff that you expect in the US for sure. Excellent central location and just a walk away from the...\n\n\nMore', u"I didn't give it 5 stars because it isn't the Ritz or Four Seasons, but if you are looking for a hotel that does not have all that hustle and bustle ,this is the place to stay.\nI have been to Chicago for business and fun numerous times. I have always stayed in hotels on Michigan Ave.\nMy wife &...\n\n\nMore", u'This upscale boutique hotel has clean, contemporary and well appointed rooms with free wifi, Keurig coffee makers and floor to ceiling windows that provide lots of light and views of the city. Security is excellent, with a second floor lobby and key-activated elevators for access to rooms. It offers a full service spa, well equipped exercise room, main floor restaurant/bar...\n\n\nMore', u"Great staff from the front door and valet to the cleaning crew. Everyone was professional and extremely helpful. I have stayed here numerous times and I'm never disappointed. Location is in the heart of the best restaurants and shopping. As far as the rooms, they are stellar. shower makes you not want to get out. I typically don't sleep well...\n\n\nMore", u'Highly recommend the spa, we were upgraded for anniversary - great time except for our neighbors loud rap music\nWe complained several times - each time got different response - put on hold- or lied to by staff- finally room was vacated but different music and different people returned at 3am again disrupting our stay-', u'First time staying at this hotel. Loved the double balconies. The bathroom was modern, clean and perfect size. The only issue I had was that my room was not ready upon check in. I arrived at 4pm and had to wait 30 minutes at the bar until my room was ready.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-fw/05/84/cb/4d/lobby--v790878.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'4070', 'title': u'Sheraton Grand Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'301 East North Water Street, Chicago, IL 60611 (Formerly Sheraton Chicago Hotel and Towers)', 'review_list': [u'Had a great stay at the Sheraton Grand Chicago. Beautiful hotel, great location, gracious staff. Kind of limited in dining options in the evening, but there are plenty of options.in the neighborhood. A good stay.', u"We spent one night in the hotel on a very cold winter. We got an amazing price through the hotel's website. Our room included the club room. Our room was clean and spacious enough to accommodate four. Our room was very quiet. I'm not sure if the hotel is always so quiet but there were very few people staying there...\n\n\nMore", u"Stayed here the past couple years for a work conference. The hotel has always treated us well. They are accommodating and make our stays easy. They could pay. Little more attention to detail on the cleaning of the rooms no bathrooms as our room was dirty when we checked in. Only reason I didn't give the hotel 5 stars", u'Stayed for 4 nights; beds and pillows were top notch; very friendly staff, especially at the lobby bar, the waitresses were lovely!\nService has been very good and guys outside calling for taxi if you need one.\nI will be back for sure and have a great time again!', u'This was a lovely hotel with great service and in the best location! Our room had a great view of the river. We were walking distance to lots of places and close to the bus. Close to the Magnificent Mile and the Institute of Art.', u"What a wonderful place to stay in the city. Can walk to many great sights and restaurants. The weather could've been better, but they can't control that. Shulas was awesome. Had a groom with an awesome view, too.", u'This is a very nice hotel in the heart of downtown. We had a quick walk or Uber everywhere we wanted to go. The bed are super comfortable and the room was quiet and nicely decorated. The lobby bar was a nice open spot with plenty of tables for a drink. Manny the bartender was very nice. We would stay...\n\n\nMore', u'I have stayed here a few times. I only use it as a last resort. Very large hotel. Rooms are nice but service can be slow. Cab lines can be very long and because of the location, a cab can be necessary. Breakfast can be very crowded and slow.', u"We live in Willowbrook, IL and sometimes we stay at SPG properties on the weekends to take our 4 year old daughter swimming, go to a nice dinner, etc. Sheraton Grand Chicago is a great hotel where everybody's super accommodating and friendly. We did get a nice room with the views of lake Michigan. Bottom line, stay there if you...\n\n\nMore", u'We were at the Sheraton for a convention. The staff is wonderful. Even though it was an extremely busy time, all of the employees did a wonderful job and were always very, very nice.\nOur room was pretty standard for a convention hotel, but it is showing its age. Our windows were covered in condensation every morning, and one morning...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://static.tacdn.com/img2/x.gif'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1736', 'title': u'Waldorf Astoria Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'5.0', 'address': u'11 East Walton, Chicago, IL 60611 (Formerly Elysian Hotel Chicago)', 'review_list': [u'The Waldorf is an amazing hotel. The rooms are very large and well appointed. The courtesy car was another great perk. Believe it is the best high-end property in Chicago. We will for sure be returning for our travels to Chicago!', u"My wife and I had never been to Chicago together until this trip. We've been back a few times since but we always say the best part of Chicago (after the deep dish pizza) is staying at the Waldorf Astoria. Wonderful rooms, excellent service and so close to so much. It is romantic and warm even when it is snowing...\n\n\nMore", u'This was the perfect location to celebrate a 50th birthday with girlfriends. The hotel and our room were both absolutely beautiful The staff were all extremely accomodating and very willing to ensure that all of our needs were met. Prior to arrival, the concierge sent an email asking if there were any special requests they should be aware of prior...\n\n\nMore', u"You can't go wrong with this hotel. I want to give it 5 stars, but the computer is not letting me. Great location and tremendous service. The waitress in the restaurant was very personable and the food amazing. Ask for a room with a balcony. The suites are all wonderful, but they can be dark when the sun is not...\n\n\nMore", u'Was expecting a wonderful experience, but it was an ordinary stay in a good hotel. The suite we had was very comfortable, and had a large balcony with seating. It overlooked a parking garage though. We were in the Gold Coast Suite.\nThe in-room breakfast was very good, and they were able to give me vegetarian breakfast potatoes, cooked with...\n\n\nMore', u"I do not know where to begin with this review. My actual intent is to talk about the restaurant--Balsan (although the name will be changing shortly).\nI am all into breakfast and I have now found the most unique, exclusive, high end breakfast you can experience in the five star hotel circle downtown Chicago--it's at the Waldorf.\nThe atmosphere is...\n\n\nMore", u'The first impression of the hotel was already fantastic. Kind and helpful staff at the desk and the rooms were clean and big. We stayed here in February when the weather was very cold but as soon as you came in to the lobby it was warm and cozy. Breakfast is great, there is not much to choose from the...\n\n\nMore', u'Excellent first class hotel. Every thing we needed was taken care of. The room and service was absolutely top of the line! We really enjoyed the location of the hotel and its proximity to high end shopping and excellent local restaurants.', u"This is my second visit to this outstanding property while on business. The hotel is classically beautiful, elegant and maintained impeccably well. The rooms are gracious and beautiful. I've been recognized as a diamond member on both visits and offered upgrade. The service and staff it outstanding. The fitness club and lounge/bar are fantastic. The Gold Coast neighborhood is alive...\n\n\nMore", u'From check-in to check-out, our stay at the Waldorf was fantastic! This is a very nice luxury hotel with wonderful service. The only bad part was that we were there for one night! I had looked at several downtown hotels to stay at while there and I am extremely happy that I selected the Waldorf! We were warmly greeted at...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/09/8a/46/bf/waldorf-astoria-chicago.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2804', 'title': u'The Gwen, a Luxury Collection Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'521 North Rush Street, at Michigan Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611 (Formerly Conrad Chicago)', 'review_list': [u'Was a weird visit because they are remodeling. Lobby is weird/small and how the hotel is setup in general is strange. I made the comment that it felt like we were in the twilite zone. It was clean and room was adequate. I am sure it would be a better experience if the remodel was completed.', u"Stayed here for just one night. Parking is easy in the lot across the street, but it's not the cheapest. Very nice interior but I guess they are in the middle of a remodel so I suspect it will be even nicer when they are done.\nLocation is amazing. We walked to a restaurant on Michigan Avenue the first night...\n\n\nMore", u"Stayed here for a couple of nights recently and enjoyed the experience. They are doing a refurbishment at present but it doesn't really impact on the stay. Rooms are well laid out and comfortable and a good size. The food is pretty varied and I enjoyed it. Overall a nice experience and would happily return.", u"I thoroughly enjoyed my stay at The Gwen last weekend. I've stayed there many times in the past when it was the Conrad Hilton and it has always been one of my favorite hotels. Luckily, the beds and bedding are the same...I've truly never slept in a more comfortable bed and the sheets are like heaven. The room sizes are...\n\n\nMore", u'What a beautiful hotel. My hubby and I love picking different hotels on our trips into Chicago. We were so happy with this choice. Location was great. Right off of Michigan Ave. The Gwen is also attached to a mall like group of shops, which was perfect for passing the time.\nSuch a beautiful lobby with a great lobby bar....\n\n\nMore', u'This hotel from beginning to check out was an experience. My wife and I had an amazing time. We had a junior suite on the top floor in a corner. Great views as you can see from pictures. Stayed on new years. Hotel staff was phenomenal, manager Kim was amazing in making our stay an experience. Will stay here again....\n\n\nMore', u"We booked a deluxe suite in this hotel after the New Year. So I would say that it wasn't so busy when we stayed there. This is more like a boutique hotel and I love it's location. It's closed to a lot of good restos. It is really in the heart of downtown. The big advantage of this hotel is...\n\n\nMore", u'This former Conrad is now the Gwen, a Starwood Luxury Hotel, has great rooms and meeting space. Hosted a wedding while we where there as well. The food is top notch and you are a two minute walk from Michigan Ave.', u'The property is under construction which created some minor inconveniences, however they upgraded us to a suite (we are SPG gold). There is no concierge lounge nor a lounge or restaurant, because of the construction. There is a temp lounge and they do serve breakfast, although it was your basic continental. If you bring your own vehicle it is very...\n\n\nMore', u'We were there over Christmas. The hotel had a boutique feel to it that was quite pleasant. We booked a Deluxe Suite and supposedly were upgraded to a grand Deluxe corner suite. The room was extremely large with two bathrooms and two seating/couch areas. The setup is simple and clean but maybe a step below places like the Waldorf. I...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/09/28/a3/09/the-gwen-chicago.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'3786', 'title': u'Hilton Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'720 South Michigan Avenue, Chicago, IL 60605', 'review_list': [u'As the rooms and floors continue to be renovated the efforts are obvious. My room had a view of Navy Pier and was very comfortable for the 3 nights I was a guest. The wifi service was poor to average (maybe the old architecture won this fight). Check in process was smooth and accurate and my room was cleaned routinely...\n\n\nMore', u"I absolutely loved my stay here! The staff was friendly and helpful, the room was outstanding and everything was labeled for us to know where to go upon entry. Plenty in the area to see and do, and it's a beautiful hotel overall.", u'My wife and I had an incredible stay at the Hilton on January 17th. We were blown away with the investment a man named Emmanuel from Registration took in being genuinely happy that we returned to the Hilton to celebrate our 3rd anniversary. As he checked us in, he gave us an upgrade option to a delightful junior suite and...\n\n\nMore', u"I have stayed at this location on several occasions and love their location close to Lake Michigan, museums, parks and other attractions. The in house rests are very good but the accessibility to much of Chicago's foodie scene adds to its attributes.", u'My husband and I have stayed at this hotel 5 times, all the way from Scotland we come to this hotel. We decided that we would upgrade to a suite as was my birthday and we were staying for 5 nights we were told upgrade would be $100 dollars extra a night which with room tax came to $559.50. That...\n\n\nMore', u'The Hilton on S Michigan Ave is perfectly located in the center of the city close to monuments and parks. The staff are very friendly and helpful. The gym/pool facilities are great. However, the rooms were a bit dated and could use a refurbishment. Although they are spacious', u'I enjoyed stay at this hotel but Definitely needs upgrading which is in progress.\nStaff Very at tentative and facility nice.\nParking was ridiculously priced when you can park a block further for $35.00 all weekend. Saved $100+ to walk one block more!\nFood at 720 was ok minus the cold soup.', u'Hotel was nice. However, the thermostat was broken, as was the pull out sofa. That was disappointing. The regular wifi was awful and make it very difficult to work. The hotel staff was responsive, but then failed to follow through until multiple requests happened or made errors in responding. We enjoyed having the suite and the executive lounge was nice,...\n\n\nMore', u"Stayed here for 5 nights while in town for work. I usually don't stay at Hilton hotels, Im more of a Marriott/Wyndam type in my personal time but since my company was footing the bill, I go where they book me. I think Im gunna change where I stay from now on. This hotel was great!! I flew in early...\n\n\nMore", u"It is a great hotel don't get me wrong but the beds weren't comfortable at all and my wife and I were on our honeymoon and not that we expected the red carpet treatment but just something. But it is a great location and beautiful inside close to almost everything in the city. (I don't wright reviews but when i...\n\n\nMore"], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/09/8a/45/42/hilton-chicago.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1379', 'title': u'Comfort Suites Michigan Avenue / Loop Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'320 North Michigan Avenue, Chicago, IL 60601', 'review_list': [u'Hotel lobby is very small - but who needs a big lobby in Chicago? - you better not be hanging out in the lobby when in Chicago! Room size was actually quite large - we had a great view looking North of Michigan Ave with a fresh snow. Easy walking distance to the big stores on Michigan while staying out...\n\n\nMore', u'Great location and reasonable price. The suite had a nice view of the river and was convenient to restaurants, shopping, Millenial Park, and The Art Institute. Included breakfast was perfect for grab and go, and the room was clean. It was a great home base for a fun girls weekend in the city.', u'We were in Chicago to see a musical at the Oriental Theater. This was a great hotel; we walked to the theater and restaurants. We were pleasantly surprised with a free upgrade to a huge corner room on the 19th floor with wonderful views of Michigan Avenue--Millennium Park out one window and the Chicago River out the other window with...\n\n\nMore', u'Great room. All the people at the desk were very pleasant, very helpful and very professional. I have already recommended it to friends. Kind of a silly requirement that I have to keep typing until I get to 200 characters.\nBut the people were still good.', u'I had a one bedroom suite on the 9th floor. I chose a one bedroom, suite because we are a couple traveling with one other person.\nPros: Location was great and central to everything. We literally walked everywhere. Our view was great, a lot of natural light and windows facing the city. The room itself was very clean, spacious and...\n\n\nMore', u"The building is very tall (26 floors) and narrow approx. 5 rooms per floor. The hotel is in a great location (at the loop, which is 45 minute subway from O'Hare in addition to a 10 minute walk from the closest station). With the hotel right in the downtown core, it is within walking distance of most key attractions. Free...\n\n\nMore", u'Good hotel on Michigan avenue without paying over-the-top. The overall quality of the rooms are good, and the staff was very helpful. We were able to easily get to all the events we went to see and shopping near by.', u'Excellent central accommodation - good location for shopping and sightseeing. Suite had lots of facilities. Staff were very helpful and polite. Would not hesitate to stay here again on a future visit to Chicago.', u'We were blown away by the size of the room, all the amenities, the price. What a neat hotel. The staff...Tian, Myron, Jason, David and Jamila were awesome. The staff directed us where to eat (Thank you) and were very friendly. We will be back and will recommend. You are a diamond in a rough.', u'Went here for a weekend to enjoy downtown Chicago. I have lived in this city my entire life and my sister and I decided to get a room for the weekend to be able to explore downtown without a vehicle!\nGot a suite with the Queen bed, ended up on the 19th floor with an amazing view! Plenty of space....\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/08/d0/c4/73/comfort-suites-michigan.jpg', 'class': u'3.0'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2155', 'title': u'Embassy Suites by Hilton Chicago Downtown Magnificent Mile Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'511 North Columbus Drive, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'My wife and I stayed here for 3 nights and had an amazing time. The cooked to order breakfast was wonderful. The line to get your breakfast can get long but the cooks are pretty fast! My eggs came out great every time. Evening reception was also great, my drink of choice was whiskey sour and the bartender made it...\n\n\nMore', u"I hav\nen't stayed at this hotel in a few years and it was great. Rooms are in good condition. I had a view of the lake.\nBreakfast is great- don't worry about the crowd- it moves fast. Take the time to go to the Made to Order area- eggs, pancakes, sausage, bacon etc- much warmer and prepared just how...\n\n\nMore", u'We have stayed at this Embassy Suites before and enjoyed it very much. The location was great - surrounded by great Chicago restaurants, a block or two from the Magnificent Mile. The rooms were superior. The amenities were more than adequate. And the service was unbeatable. This stay, however, was marred by a frustrating breakfast experience. This large hotel was...\n\n\nMore', u'Stayed in this great hotel for a "Girls Weekend". We had very spacious adjoining rooms that were well appointed, beds very comfortable. This hotel is very convenient to good restaurants, shopping and not a bad walk to the theater district, even in January! Cocktail hour was ok snacks minimal, chex mix and corn chips with cheese dip. Wine was also...\n\n\nMore', u'The location is perfect! You can walk to the main attractions such as Navy\u2019s pier, Willis Tower, Millennium Park, Michigan ave all are within few kms. And the staff are so friendly and helpful! We started our happy day from enjoying the breakfast and seeing the great staff \u2013 Maymay Jiang. She is working at serving Omlet area, we had...\n\n\nMore', u'Whirlwind 48 hours in Chicago! From this location, walked to the Navy Pier (3 blocks) and to the NBC Studios (1 block). The room at Embassy Suites was very comfortable, clean and quiet. Minus- the evening reception... potato chips, raw vegetables and dip, soft drinks and 1 free alcoholic beverage. Was disappointed. Breakfast on the other hand was great. Made...\n\n\nMore', u"Looks nice and shiny from the outside but the rest is just okay don't expect to much unless they you buy in for the upsell. Pros Breakfast and the 5 Pm soiree. Rooms was great for the government rate but 20 came in so they got their moneys worth. Cons Internet was so bad couldn't get any work done.", u'From the Valet to the departure the staff was all helpful and friendly. Our rooms where very comfortable and clean. the only issues I had(my fault) the valet parking price is ridiculous @ 63.00. The breakfast was sub-par at best, but it was free.? I could have parked down the street for 33.00 I found out after the fact. I...\n\n\nMore', u"Embassy Suites is the perfect location to spend with Family and/or Friends on New Years Eve. We requested a room facing the lake and were able to watch the fireworks from Navy's pier right from our bedroom window. Which was perfect because it was quiet cold and we had kids with us.\nThe morning complimentary breakfast was great. And the...\n\n\nMore", u'I loved the stay. The hotel is fantastic.\nThe location is at downtown and you can enjoy Chicago downtown. All the major attractions are within few kms.\nYou can enjoy the morning buffet and I bet you will enjoy it whatever your breakfast preference is.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/08/2e/3f/02/embassy-suites-by-hilton.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1781', 'title': u'theWit - A DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'201 N. State Street, Chicago, IL 60601', 'review_list': [u"I booked this hotel last August to celebrate my 21st birthday because of the Rooftop bar! We live like 2 hours away so it's kind of a long drive. My sister and I got all ready for the bar and we were so excited we got our name on the list and everything. As I said before I just turned...\n\n\nMore", u"We stayed here early in Jan. for a wedding. The easy access to theaters and Michigan Ave. was nice. Price was also reasonable given the location and room amenities. However, parking was pricey and remote if you wanted to self park, as the lots closest to the hotel were closed on the weekend we stayed there. Tough, when you're hauling...\n\n\nMore", u'We stayed here because of a wedding.\nWhen we arrived check-in was a breeze with the help of Adam our front desk person.\nThe warm cookies were a nice touch.\nThe room, shower and bathroom was very roomy and at no time did we feel cramped.\nGreat views of the city.\nThe rooftop lounge is a must see and visit....\n\n\nMore', u"I have to say, this is one of my favorite hotel stays. Despite my need to get work done instead of going out to enjoy the city, I did really enjoy staying in this hotel and look forward to another visit.\nFirst, it's location. It's right along the river, has the loop adjacent to it for quick travel, and is...\n\n\nMore", u"What the Wit lacks in size compared to other Hilton's it makes up for in price and value. Service was top notch-we had an immediate response to a maintenance request on a busy Friday night. We all decided the beds were 5 stars for comfort. And if you're going to the theater, you can not beat the location. Park your...\n\n\nMore", u"Well lets start at the beginning our check in was awful and I'm not going to go in to detail as they took care of the problems and went above and beyond and I am very grateful for what they did. The hotel and rooms look amazing great styling. The roof top club/bar is nice it was dead when we...\n\n\nMore", u"The hotel website advertised a rooftop bar...not a club. It was definitely a club. Tons of visitors going in and out of the lobby and holding up the elevators. Granted, everyone likes a little clubbing action...just maybe not in the same hotel I'm supposed to stay at.", u'The staff was very welcoming, friendly and accomodating. The corner room was lovely on the 21st floor with large windows overlookig the Chicago River. I felt homesick for the Wit when I returned to my actual home!', u'Great area for a hotel, within walking distance to lots of good restaurants and shopping. Great rooftop bar and view of the city. It was winter, so it was cold, but rooftop was closed in and still wonderful views and lots of fun! My husband and I would definitely goi back and stay. We were here for a wedding, but...\n\n\nMore', u'Love the staff, location, restaurant and service! I felt that from the moment I arrived it was wonderful staff. The concierge service for recommendations were fabulous and I the location was so great!'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/01/a7/2e/71/thewit-street-view.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1856', 'title': u'The Westin Michigan Avenue Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.0', 'address': u'909 N. Michigan Ave., Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'I am on a long term project and spent a lot of time here. I love it! The staff is amazing, the hotel is clean, and the location is perfect! I travel a lot for work, this is one of the top hotels I ha e stayed in. To be greeted daily with a smile and a staff that cannot...\n\n\nMore', u'The Westin is a great hotel to stay. Friendly staff. Check-in was quick. Accommodates late departure time. Wonderful location. Close to several attractions and shops. Hotel room had view overlooking Michigan Ave.', u"Held a meeting at this location, stayed 3 nights.. The remodeled rooms are great! Bed comfortable, HUGE tv's in room! Great location to Michigan Avenue. Fabulous bar / restaurant attached! Staff is professional and extremely helpful!", u'I only stayed 1 night, but received emails offering assistance in advance, confirmations etc. I felt that this, coupled with a smooth check in, whereby my early check in request had been accommodated, really delivered a special, personalised feel to the service. The doughnuts and warm cider in the lobby were a great touch and the rooms nicely renovated. Not...\n\n\nMore', u'I had an amazing stay at his hotel when I was out in Chicago for work and some fun! The staff was amazing from check- in to departure. We had an amazing corner room overlooking Michigan Avenue! The hotel cares about the guest experience which was demonstrated with the concierge. Kira spent a lot of time with my friend and...\n\n\nMore', u'This hotel is centrally located to shopping, restaurants, entertainment, parks and so much more. Every member of the staff was helpful and went out of their way to help my wife and I. Would definitely recommend to others!', u'The hotel has great location; Michigan Ave is in walking distance that is convenient for shopping. We stayed during the Thanksgiving week so it might be a very out-dated review but overall the stay here was pleasant.\nBecause we stayed here for a short family gathering for Thanksgiving, we had about 3 more family groups staying at the same hotel...\n\n\nMore', u"This is my second stay at this hotel. Our room was a standard with 2 Queen beds, which was as expected. The view from the room was north looking out onto Lake Shore Drive / Lake Michigan and was spectacular. We did not request a room with a view! You can't beat the location for shopping and the best restaurants....\n\n\nMore", u'My daughter and I only stayed two nights in December 2015, but we loved the hotel. The beds were the best ever and the location of the hotel is ideal for a short stay in Chicago. It is close to everything that you would want to see. We just walked everywhere. Close to good restaurants, shops and tourist locations. Would...\n\n\nMore', u'The staff was very professional and eager to assist me upon walking into the lobby.\nThe location of this hotel is very convenient to shopping and good restaurants. They have a restaurant connected to the hotel in the lobby which has great drinks and appetizers. I would definitely stay here again when visitng to Chicago.'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/07/87/03/dc/the-westin-michigan-avenue.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2546', 'title': u'The James Chicago Hotel', 'rating_string': u'4.5', 'address': u'55 East Ontario, Corner of Rush and Ontario, Chicago, IL 60611', 'review_list': [u'We stayed at the James for our anniversary. The hotel is very nice and equipped with a nice lobby with a sleek bar. The steakhouse in the hotel was very good and I would highly recommend it. The rooms were great and affordable. We ended up with the King Loft which was nice and spacious. The room came with an...\n\n\nMore', u'Our stay was great! The hotel is in a wonderful location right by Michigan Ave. There is so much to do around that area and everything is clean and pleasing. The staff was amazing and provided top-notch service. Would reccomend highly!!!', u'Everything was excellent. We took advantage of a package deal for a King Apartment which included free breakfast for 2 and free valet parking. Room was clean, spacious and had all the amenities you would expect. The in-room breakfast was amazing, which was followed by in-room massages(reasonably priced and worth every penny). What a great way to start your day...\n\n\nMore', u"I live in Chicago, but stayed here with family who were visiting from out of town. The location is really great, you are right in the middle of the action and walking distance to everything. Many amenities right across the street, including Starbucks, Trader Joe's, and a bank. Lobby is nice, and the bar is great. The rooms need updating....\n\n\nMore", u'My husband and I recently stayed at the James Hotel in Chicago. We had been recommended by a friend to stay here, and we were happy with everything! The rooms were big, clean, and the beds were so freaking comfortable! We will definetely be back.', u'I recommend paying for the larger suite - there is so much extra room. I think the staff was incredibly friendly and helpful. The hotel is perfectly centrally located and there is a Trader Joes across the street so you can stock up on munchies. I have stayed here many times and I would stay here again.', u"Clean, neat, excellent service.\nAccomodations were trendy and upscale\nHotel's restaurant was a 5 star to us\nElevetors were little crowdy but everything else was top notch\nThis is the second time we have stayed here", u"For what I paid, I was not impressed. Front desk didn't notify me of the hefty incidental charges, prior to charging me. Mirror in bathroom was broken. Light nobs were falling off. Couch in king guest had a broken leg. Cold bath water for 20 minutes. Staff was fine, but they really didn't care about my concerns. Once in a...\n\n\nMore", u'The James Chicago is in an ideal location, close to shopping, transit options, great restaurants and a block from Michigan Avenue. Our room was exceptional: large, comfortable, well equipped and extremely cost reasonable. staff were both friendly and helpful. i will definitely return.', u"It's my 2nd time here for an annual convention. Stayed here last year and the bath tub back washed while I wasn't in the room which remained some ugly scene. They upgraded me to another room the next day. This time, the toilet was clogged and I had to run down to the 2nd floor in the middle of the...\n\n\nMore"], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/07/7a/8e/40/loft-suite.jpg'}
