{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'2', 'title': u'Lincoln Motel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'1.0', 'address': u'5900 N. Lincoln Ave, Chicago, IL 60659', 'review_list': [u"The rooms smell of dirt,you can't turn off the heat. can't open the windows. the fitted sheets on the beds are not clean.blood on them and turned inside out. house cleaning workers are very lazy, and one clerk hindu guy very,very rude to customers. they invested a lot into key less doors, but every thing else is bad this hotel...\n\n\nMore", u"Stayed here with a friend of mine in July 2004 because most of the regular motels and hotels are ridiculously expensive near downtown Chicago ($130/night for a Super 8 motel?!). I knew it would be an adventure, but I didn't expect the lighted and MIRRORED ceiling. In fact, mirrors covered nearly every wall of the room. Very disturbing. The cigarette...\n\n\nMore"], 'img_url': ''}
