{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'45', 'title': u'Midway Inn Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'1.5', 'address': u'5335 S Pulaski Rd, Chicago, IL 60632', 'review_list': [u"Bed bugs and dingy. But, $66 including tax and 2 miles from ($6 Uber trip) Midway airport. In a seedy neighborhood. Don't bring your kids here. But, if you need a cheap room and don't mind bed bugs- go for it!", u"The hotel has no heat, electricity doesn't work, they have cords running from 1 outlet that's hooks up to the tv, the heater, the frig, the lamp, etc, this nasty hotel also has roaches, house keeping don't clean up, the toilet doesn't flush right, the people at the front desk acts like they don't know nothing, the microwave stays nasty,...\n\n\nMore", u'is easily accessible by drive/taxi. It has free parking, and internet. the rooms are basic, with shampoo/shower gel off the dispensers, the beds and bathroom is very basic. the breakfast consists of dunking donut sandwiches, and an automated pancake machine. The staff is friendly, and they do a good job making the room everyday. There is complimentary shuttle services for...\n\n\nMore', u"Free porn. Concierge is awesome!!!!! Cheap. Cheap. Cheap. Close to the train station so that was awesome. Cheap. Did I mention cheap and porn. Did feel concerned that I might get murdered while I was there but I'm still alive and made it back to Texas. Lollapalooza was blast.", u"I travel for work weekly, so I'm in hotels a lot. This is perhaps the WORST I ever had the displeasure of staying in. No air conditioning, dirty/scroungy condition, the internet works great RIGHT in the lobby.. but you won't get a signal in your room (despite high speed internet being prominently displayed on their sign as a reason to...\n\n\nMore", u"The only reason we stayed here was my fianc\xe9e had to much to drink and couldn't drive back to Orland park so we needed a place to sleep it off. It was -10 degrees but we would have been better off sleeping in the car. There was no heat! The room was dirty and freezing. The curtains were half pulled...\n\n\nMore", u"This was the most disgusting Hotel I have ever stayed at. I should have never rented but when I went back down to get a refund they would not give it back. They claim they do not give refunds!!!! We struggled for 2 hours to try and sleep but just couldn't handle it. The room had no heat, there was...\n\n\nMore", u'disgusting and horrible!!! poor customer services & the room literally had 12 roaches around the tv stand when complained the staff put us in a room worest than first one this place should be shut down! the hallway had garbage overflown & the rooms had electric heaters on the floor i do not recommend this dump!!', u"Well me and my mother checked inn and some strangerwas going around asking for vicadons! The a/c didn't work! The floor in the second room after complaning about the first room was all wet and sticky and one spot had a white stains! The windows weren't even clean! We did not feel safe nor confortable here so we got a...\n\n\nMore", u'Firstly we had some issues with the check-in, after that no internet in the room!! And the worst, 2 days after our arriving,i was bitten by BED BUGS!!!!!! The first time of my life, i was allergic so i had so many spots on my legs and on my arms!!! It was horrible!\nJust 1 advice : NEVER, NEVER SLEEP...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/08/bf/a4/91/midway-inn.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'11', 'title': u'Milshire Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'1.5', 'address': u'2525 N. Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60647', 'review_list': [u"I've stayed at a lot of bad places but this was the worst\nI got bed bug bites alll over", u"The place is really bad, as described in pretty much every review.\nI'd like to confirm, yes, there are few roaches, but also plenty of BEDBUGS. Roaches will maybe crawl up on you in you sleep, but ultimately won't come home with you. They love this HO(tel). But bedbugs will ! and will infest every piece of wood in your...\n\n\nMore", u"I've stayed at some run down places all over the world, but this place takes the cake. First off it is a brothel, and filled with meth/crack heads. I have no idea how this place passes any inspections. I was going to a couple of shows at the Congress theater, and this place is the closest place to it, so...\n\n\nMore", u"After reading the reviews online about this hotel, anyone would think this is a horrible place to stay. The reality, however, is that it really isn't that bad! My husband and I were pleasantly surprised by our experience here. If you're looking for a poshy place to stay, this is not it. But if you're looking for hostel quality, you'll...\n\n\nMore", u'We got into the lobby and two guys were in the reception enclosure area. One of the guys was wearing a heavy metal shirt that read psycho-something. For a double room it was only $40 so we figured we are only staying the night so no big deal, right? So we got a room key and got buzzed into the...\n\n\nMore', u'This place looks more like a brothel than a hotel. The "receptionist" has to see every person who is going to stay before give you the key. Once you get to the room is like a puzzle to open the door. Then the room is disgusting, you\'ll see the rep carpet with thousands of spots, I didn\'t even use the...\n\n\nMore', u'I travel a lot and stay in some pretty shady places but this one took the cake. Cockroaches everywhere, smells nasty, Mrs Roper receptionist, doubles as brothel, dirtiest hotel I have every seen, broken doors, old food that looked like a mix of cigarette butts and corn in the plant in front of our door, fat shirtless white trash guy...\n\n\nMore', u"This place does seem older but it has charcter like the Chelsea without all the famous guests. Being a tourist I did feel uncomfortable sleeping and I didn't like leaving the key at the desk when we left.. We were attending a concert at the Double Door.", u'When we got there, we had to choose a room with a "private bath". The receptionist is hidden behind a glass wall, the announcements on the walls are written with a pen and she has to buzz you in to get into the hotel lobby.\nThe place smells bad, the elevator is probably the original (1930\'s?).When we got to the...\n\n\nMore', u'My friend and I decided to stay here for one night to attend a concert at the Congress Theatre ($48/nite). The neighborhood is kind of rundown until you turn the corner and there are these lush, posh areas. The location was convenient, access to the busline and within 15 min walking distance to where we wanted to go. There were...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://static.tacdn.com/img2/x.gif'}
