{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'26', 'title': u'Sheffield House Motel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'2.0', 'address': u'3834 N. Sheffield Ave, Chicago, IL 60613', 'review_list': [u'We planned our trip up to chicago a month before so we booked the closest hotel near wrigley field for the cubs vs. marlins game, when we got to the hotel the lady had to go clean our room first mind you this was at check in, so it should have been done. we got to the room finally our...\n\n\nMore', u"Ever seen one of those movies with the flickering bathroom light as the rock bottom heroine addict shoots up one last time before dying with the hose still wrapped around his arm? I think they shoot all those scenes at the Sheffield House. Before booking your room, call your doctor and give him a heads up that you'll be needing...\n\n\nMore", u'bath yellow, bath door not shutting, no phone, blinds falling off window, bed made, but underneath stains (fresh) as per the crumbs of food also there, floor dirty, no pictures on wall, smelly, towels folded wet ... agreed to a new room and manager refused ... we left and they did not refund our money at $80 a night ......\n\n\nMore', u'When I first arrived at the Sheffield House I was in awe of its superb location and it\'s charming characteristics. I walked in to an extrememly pleasant woman at the front desk. Although she sounded like "Ma" from Ma\'s Roudhouse, I didn\'t mind. I found it pleasurable. She escorted me to a lovely little room which I found to be...\n\n\nMore', u'This place was horrifying. My girlfriend and I were traveling to chicago on short notice to catch a cubs game. This happened to be the only place that had available space. We struggled to find parking upon our arrival and when we asked the lady at the front desk she said we had to talk to "someone" down the street...\n\n\nMore', u'This place is by far the worst place i have ever stayed in my life. I went along with two friends for the cardinals vs cubs game. It was the only place we could get a reservation at since we decided to go up so late and i would have rathered sleep in the car than in this place. Before...\n\n\nMore', u'Scary. The lady/owner asked my wife when we arrived if she was there to "work". That pretty much summed it all up. Parking and location were great though. If you\'re a thrill seeker , drug addict or loved the movie "Se7en" then you may enjoy it. Oh, and no phone. I had water for a shower, but my wife was...\n\n\nMore', u'Was visiting Chicago for the Cubs/Sox Series and the Blues festival.\nPerfect location to get around, love the neighborhood.\nFront desk was very helpful.', u'Me and my boyfriend arrived in chicago with the intention to stay at the Sheffield House. We were really excited about the perfect location, walking distance of everything (including a cheap and amazing bakery for breakfast just north a block on the opposite side of the street ) and after a day of traveling we just wanted to drop off...\n\n\nMore', u"This was the worst motel I've ever been too. It was so bad, I Googled it just to find a website to write a review about it to; other people need to know, too. Our bed didn't even have a fitted sheet, just two sheets and a blanket. They wouldn't give us extra pillows or blankets. There was no remote...\n\n\nMore"], 'img_url': u'http://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-w/01/11/f4/09/chicago.jpg'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'11', 'title': u'Skylark Motel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'1.5', 'address': u'5435 S Archer Ave, Chicago, IL 60638', 'review_list': [u"My family got stranded at MDW for the night and couldn't find any hotels with vacancies in the area. After talking with a lady at the airport so directs taxi cabs at curbside, telling her our problem, she said that the Skylark Motel is around the corner....I called the office and we were in luck, they had rooms. We took...\n\n\nMore", u"I stayed at this motel a few weeks ago and despite everyone's negative reviews, I think this a good value for the price. The staff was friendly and helpful. The room was surprisingly clean and the bed was comfortable. Even though the area of the motel may not be the best (that's why they have police ordered signs to keep...\n\n\nMore", u'Just needed somewhere to stay for the night while we were in town. Expedia set us up with this room over the phone so we had no pictures of the place or anything . We figured a room for 100 dollars would be decent enough to just sleep in. We arrive at the motel hoping the rooms look better than...\n\n\nMore', u"Door knob on bathroom door was broken, there was a crack in the mirror, the lights flickered, the TV had like 6 channels, but if you like hardcore porn, then you're in luck, it's on channel four. The day we left we turned on the heater (held to the wall with duct tape) and it popped and started smoking. We...\n\n\nMore", u'I would have rated this place NO stars if it had let me!\nWe were just looking a place that was close to the airport and was relatively cheap. We should have known as soon as we were dropped off at this place what we were in for. The reception area is littered with signs saying "No prostitution allowed". Definitely...\n\n\nMore', u'We just needed a place to crash, while our heater got fixed\nwe are locals and learned the hard way about this place\nfirst of, the place is so unsecure, the doors are very flimsy...not a clean place... to place your head on the pillows, no!!!... and when my honey decided to place one of the chairs against the door,...\n\n\nMore', u'Where do I begin.....\nMy teenage son and I decided to take a last-minute excursion from Columbus, OH to Chicago in early August 2008. Our plan was to see the Planetarium, Sears Tower, Chinatown, the Navy Pier,take an evening boat ride on Lake Michigan, then head back home. Two days were plenty for all this.\nI looked online at Hotels.com....\n\n\nMore', u"We were passing through Chicago on our way to New York and thought we would stay for 1 night. We were on our honeymoon and booked everything as we went along. We decided to stay at the Skylark because it was quite cheap and didn't look too bad on the internet. When we got to our room we were shocked...\n\n\nMore", u"We needed a place to stay at for the night, so we wanted a cheap hotel, but we couldn't find any so we stayed at this place for $75 or so.\nFirst thing we noticed is there was no lock on the door and was ripped off, so we put a large desk in front of the door, because we...\n\n\nMore", u'My mother booked this hotel after as we had an early morning flight out. It was one of the most horrifying experiences of my life. My first clue should have been the fact that the front desk clerk sat behind bullet proof glass. The second was the kick marks on the front door. There were holes in the wall and...\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': u'http://static.tacdn.com/img2/x.gif'}
{'category': 'hotel', 'review_count': u'1', 'title': u'Stan Properties Suites at 300 N. Canal Hotel, Chicago', 'rating_string': u'1.0', 'address': u'300 N. Canal Street, Chicago, IL 60654', 'review_list': [u'I stayed at the South Water location, and it was terrible from the moment we opened the door. The cleaning man was just starting to clean well after the check-in time, but hardly did anything. The apartment was filthy. Stained carpets (not just a spot, but as though there was a coffee and wine fight!), marked-up walls, and dirty counters....\n\n\nMore'], 'img_url': ''}
